# CLAUDE.md — VB Tippjáték 2026

World Cup 2026 prediction game for ~35 friends. Vanilla JS, no build step. Backend: Convex. Hosted on Cloudflare. Current version: **v1.3.0**.

---

## Run & deploy

```bash
# Frontend: any static server from repo root
# Backend:
npx convex dev      # local (typechecks, generates _generated/)
npx convex deploy   # production

# Syntax check after any JS edit (template literals silently break tabs):
node --check js/<file>.js
```

Secrets live in **Convex env vars only** — never in the repo:
`LS_KEY`, `LS_SECRET`, `VAPID_PRIVATE`, `VAPID_EMAIL`

---

## Architecture

```
Convex crons (livescore.ts) ──poll──▶ apiCache table
Convex subscriptions        ──push──▶ convex-bridge.js ──▶ store.js (state={})
                                                               │
UI mutations: window.cvxMut('module:fn', args)                 ▼
                                            render-*.js ◀──reads── state.* + data.js globals
                                                 │
                                            ui.js / sync.js (tab switch, polling, toasts)
```

**The browser never calls the live-score API directly.** All polling is server-side via Convex cron.

---

## JS load order (order matters — renderers need globals)

```
data.js → bracket.js → livescore.js → config.js → convex-bridge.js (ES module) →
util.js → store.js → scoring.js →
render-leaderboard → render-predictions → render-wizard → render-swiss →
render-matchcentre → render-groups → render-profile → changelog →
render-about → admin-totp → admin-txnlog → admin-core →
game-actions → notify → sync → ui → app
```

`sw.js` keeps a copy of this list — keep them in sync or offline users 404 on new files.

